cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) because it deals with natural language processing and understanding user service intentions. It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves the use of intelligent systems to provide personalized services. The use of neural networks in the proposed model makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. The paper also involves information retrieval and classification, which could place it in cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-categories.
